{"tag":"section","attrib":{"id":"idbd35aec9-47c4-11f1-bea6-82cea744851c","identifier":"/us/usc/t31/s3552"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"3552"},"text":"§ 3552.","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" Protests by interested parties concerning procurement actions","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"subsection","attrib":{"id":"idbd35aeca-47c4-11f1-bea6-82cea744851c","identifier":"/us/usc/t31/s3552/a"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"a"},"text":"(a)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" A protest concerning an alleged violation of a procurement statute or regulation shall be decided by the Comptroller General if filed in accordance with this subchapter.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subsection","attrib":{"id":"idbd35aecb-47c4-11f1-bea6-82cea744851c","identifier":"/us/usc/t31/s3552/b"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"b"},"text":"(b)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"idbd35aecc-47c4-11f1-bea6-82cea744851c","identifier":"/us/usc/t31/s3552/b/1"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"1"},"text":"(1)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" In the case of an agency tender official who is an interested party under ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t31/s3551/2/B"},"text":"section 3551(2)(B) of this title","children":[],"tail":", the official may file a protest in connection with the public-private competition for which the official is an interested party. At the request of a majority of the employees of the Federal agency who are engaged in the performance of the activity or function subject to such public-private competition, the official shall file a protest in connection with such public-private competition unless the official determines that there is no reasonable basis for the protest."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"idbd35aecd-47c4-11f1-bea6-82cea744851c","identifier":"/us/usc/t31/s3552/b/2"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"2"},"text":"(2)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" The determination of an agency tender official under paragraph (1) whether or not to file a protest is not subject to administrative or judicial review. An agency tender official shall provide written notification to Congress whenever the official makes a determination under paragraph (1) that there is no reasonable basis for a protest.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"sourceCredit","attrib":{"id":"idbd35aece-47c4-11f1-bea6-82cea744851c"},"text":"(Added ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/98/369/dB/tVII/s2741/a"},"text":"Pub. L. 98–369, div. B, title VII, § 2741(a)","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1984-07-18"},"text":"July 18, 1984","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/98/1199"},"text":"98 Stat. 1199","children":[],"tail":"; amended "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/103/272/s4/f/1/L"},"text":"Pub. L. 103–272, § 4(f)(1)(L)","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1994-07-05"},"text":"July 5, 1994","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/108/1362"},"text":"108 Stat. 1362","children":[],"tail":"; "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/103/355/tX/s10005/d"},"text":"Pub. L. 103–355, title X, § 10005(d)","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1994-10-13"},"text":"Oct. 13, 1994","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/108/3408"},"text":"108 Stat. 3408","children":[],"tail":"; "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/104/106/dE/tLVI/s5603"},"text":"Pub. L. 104–106, div. E, title LVI, § 5603","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1996-02-10"},"text":"Feb. 10, 1996","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/110/700"},"text":"110 Stat. 700","children":[],"tail":"; "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/108/375/dA/tIII/s326/b"},"text":"Pub. L. 108–375, div. A, title III, § 326(b)","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2004-10-28"},"text":"Oct. 28, 2004","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/118/1848"},"text":"118 Stat. 1848","children":[],"tail":".)"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"notes","attrib":{"type":"uscNote","id":"idbd35aecf-47c4-11f1-bea6-82cea744851c"},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"note","attrib":{"role":"crossHeading","topic":"editorialNotes","id":"idbd35aed0-47c4-11f1-bea6-82cea744851c"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"b","attrib":{},"text":"Editorial Notes","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"amendments","id":"idbd35aed1-47c4-11f1-bea6-82cea744851c"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Amendments","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"2004—","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/108/375"},"text":"Pub. L. 108–375","children":[],"tail":" designated existing provisions as subsec. (a) and added subsec. (b)."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"1996—","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/104/106"},"text":"Pub. L. 104–106","children":[],"tail":" struck out at end “An interested party who has filed a protest under section 111(f) of the Federal Property and Administrative Services Act of 1949 ("},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t40/s759/f"},"text":"40 U.S.C. 759(f)","children":[],"tail":") with respect to a procurement or proposed procurement may not file a protest with respect to that procurement under this subchapter.”"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"1994—","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/103/272"},"text":"Pub. L. 103–272","children":[],"tail":" and "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/103/355"},"text":"Pub. L. 103–355","children":[],"tail":" amended section identically, substituting “section 111(f)” for “section 111(h)” and “759(f)” for “759(h)”."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"role":"crossHeading","topic":"statutoryNotes","id":"idbd35aed2-47c4-11f1-bea6-82cea744851c"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"b","attrib":{},"text":"Statutory Notes and Related Subsidiaries","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"effectiveDateOfAmendment","id":"idbd35aed3-47c4-11f1-bea6-82cea744851c"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Effective Date of 2004 Amendment","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Amendment by ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/108/375"},"text":"Pub. L. 108–375","children":[],"tail":" applicable to protests filed under this subchapter that relate to studies initiated under Office of Management and Budget Circular A–76 on or after the end of the 90-day period beginning on "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2004-10-28"},"text":"Oct. 28, 2004","children":[],"tail":", see "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/108/375/s326/d"},"text":"section 326(d) of Pub. L. 108–375","children":[],"tail":", set out as a note under "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t31/s3551"},"text":"section 3551 of this title","children":[],"tail":"."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"effectiveDateOfAmendment","id":"idbd35aed4-47c4-11f1-bea6-82cea744851c"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Effective Date of 1996 Amendment","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Amendment by ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/104/106"},"text":"Pub. L. 104–106","children":[],"tail":" effective 180 days after "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1996-02-10"},"text":"Feb. 10, 1996","children":[],"tail":", see "},{"tag":"ref","at